<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; WASHINGTON, D.C.; U.S. MAY WAIVE HIV BAN FOR GAY GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Justice Department is considering a temporary waiver of a ban forbidding 
HIV-infected people to enter the United States, officials and gay activists 
said.The waiver would allow visitors infected with HIV, which causes the AIDS 
virus, to participate in the Gay Games, scheduled to take place in New York in 
June. One U.S. official, speaking on condition of anonymity, said a communique 
on the waiver had been prepared in anticipation of approval by Atty. Gen. Janet 
Reno. He said the communique had been mistakenly sent to embassies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
