<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; CANINE AS WATCHDOG IS FOCUS OF SEMINAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago College will offer a seminar Sunday on home security that will 
focus on making the family canine a better watchdog. 
</P>
<P>
 The seminar will cover methods of making dogs more alert to noises from 
intruders, to bark an alarm, stand its ground if an intruder is present and to 
patrol the house. Methods to deter unwanted barking habits also will be 
covered, said spokesman Dale Ruhe. 
</P>
<P>
 The session will be from 4 to 5:30 p.m. in Room A-2 of the Santa Ana campus, 
at 17th and Bristol streets. The fee for the seminar is $15 and people 
attending should not bring their pets. For more information, call (714) 
564-6220. JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
