<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA ROUNDUP; MASHBURN'S 37 POINTS ADD TO PROBLEMS IN CHARLOTTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With illness, injuries and Mike Gminski en route to new employment, the 
Hornets were nine-strong for their game against the Dallas Mavericks at 
Charlotte. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the missing were Larry Johnson and Alonzo Mourning. 
</P>
<P>
 Make that nine-weak. 
</P>
<P>
 Charlotte lost for the 12th time in its last 13 games, 115-110, to Dallas, 
which shot 64% in winning its second in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 Rookie Jamal Mashburn scored 37 points to lead six Mavericks in double 
figures. 
</P>
<P>
 "When a team shoots 64%, it's difficult to win," Hornet Coach Allan Bristow 
said. "Our presence inside is not what we want it to be. We've got to play 
better defense. Right now we're struggling." 
</P>
<P>
 The addition of Frank Brickowski, acquired in the Gminski deal that was a 
trade of 34-year-old players, is expected to help. 
</P>
<P>
 Houston 93, New York 73 -- Hakeem Olajuwon had 29 points and 20 rebounds, and 
made four consecutive baskets in a fourth-quarter run that carried the Rockets, 
who held the Knicks to 29 points in the second half, at home. 
</P>
<P>
 Phoenix 120, Minnesota 101 -- The Suns won for the fifth time in their last 
six games and remained unbeaten in 19 games against the Timberwolves behind 26 
points from Cedric Ceballos at Minneapolis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
