<P>
 Well, it finally happened. After we've heard about it for years. 
</P>
<P>
 In the stands at Canada's overtime hockey game the other night sat 
silver-medal figure skater Elvis Stojko, cheering for his fellow Canadians. One 
period, two periods, three periods, overtime . . . there he sat. 
</P>
<P>
 Then, about four minutes into the overtime period, Stojko, eager not to miss a 
minute of the women's figure skating, left his seat to go watch, missing the 
game-winning goal by Canada's Paul Kariya. 
</P>
<P>
 That's right, Elvis had left the building. MIKE DOWNEY 
