<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOOKS; BATTERY ON ICE: PARODY IN PRINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELIZABETH MEHREN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 You remember them: Portland's finest, the Olympic "Scheme Team." 
</P>
<P>
 There's Tonya Harding, who spent Wednesday earning unimpressive short-program 
scores in Lillehammer; Jolly Jeff Gillooly, last seen peddling topless video 
footage of his beloved ex-wife; and Shawn Eckardt (the bulging bodyguard) and 
Shane Stant -- both charged with conspiracy in the Jan. 6 attack on Nancy 
Kerrigan in Detroit. 
</P>
<P>
 Now this lovable bunch is reunited on the pages of "WHACKED! -- The Adventures 
of Tonya Harding and Her Pals," a 32-page, full-color parody comic book to be 
published in March by The River Group of Westport, Conn. It will sell for 
$2.50, with the edition limited to "as many people who want to spend that much 
to buy it," according to Alan Katz, who has written the text for this morality 
play commemorative. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the "scoops" you'll find in "WHACKED!" is Tonya's Family Scrapbook, 
featuring pictures of baby Tonya, right up to her first cigar. 
</P>
<P>
 There is also an "Ask Tonya" feature, where the U.S. National Figure Skating 
champion offers "true glimpses" of her innermost feelings. 
</P>
<P>
 Katz, who has also written for Disney's "Goof Troop" as well as a collection 
of trading cards, said "WHACKED!" avoids tramping into total tastelessness 
because "there's nothing here that you haven't seen or heard on 'A Current 
Affair' or the evening news." 
</P>
<P>
 He noted, too, that "WHACKED!" ends with a brief, but relatively sober 
discourse on winning and losing. ELIZABETH MEHREN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Book Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
