<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL SOCCER PLAYOFF ROUNDUP; BURROUGHS ADVANCES, 3-2, ON GOAL BY PEREZ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Roberto Perez scored the winning goal with 17 minutes remaining in a 
quarterfinal match of the Southern Section Division III playoffs Thursday as 
Burroughs upset Palmdale, 3-2, at Burroughs. 
</P>
<P>
 Perez, a senior forward who also scored the Indians' first goal, kicked in the 
winner on the rebound of a shot by forward Eddie Melgar, vaulting the Indians 
into the semifinals for the second consecutive season. 
</P>
<P>
 Perez has scored five goals in his last two matches. Jesus Diaz also scored 
for Burroughs (14-6-3) and goalie Marc Binda had six saves. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Dibbini and Craig Peck scored for Palmdale (22-2-2) and Falcon goalie 
Beau Cline had nine saves. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Southern Section quarterfinal matches: 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake 1, Arcadia 0 -- Striker David Tuizer scored for the host 
Wolverines (20-0-4) on a throw-in at the 23-minute mark, and goalkeeper Jay 
Rosen made six saves while recording his 14th shutout in a Division III match. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 1, La Salle 0 -- Jamie Surace scored on an assist from Jared Kira 
with a minute to play in the Division V match. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas 2, Santa Paula 1 (4-3 penalty kicks) -- Goalkeeper Mike Freedman 
recorded seven saves to lead the visiting Coyotes (13-3-4) past the defending 
Division V champions. 
</P>
<P>
 Adan Almaraz scored an unassisted goal for the Cardinals (14-6-2) 17 minutes 
into the contest, then junior halfback Darren Miller headed in Darren Cooper's 
long throw-in five minutes later to deadlock the match. 
</P>
<P>
 City Section (second round) 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys 2, Sylmar 1 -- Federico Arroyo scored both goals for the Wolves 
(10-2-2), his 17th and 18th. Jose Cortez had 12 saves for Van Nuys, which has 
made a striking turnaround from last season, when it struggled to an 1-11 
record. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell 4, Granada Hills 2 -- Corey Heimlich and Martin Felman scored for Granada 
Hills (8-5-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 2, Grant 0 -- Golden Cougar midfielder Brett Reveles scored both goals 
in overtime at Kennedy (14-3), posting one in each of the two extra periods. 
GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
 City Section (quarterfinals) 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth 2, Garfield 0 -- Kim Pickup and Krista Ogasawara scored for 
top-seeded Chatsworth (15-0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Grant 6, Bell 0 -- Nicole Bucciarelli recorded a hat trick as Grant (11-3-2) 
dealt Bell (15-1) its first defeat. 
</P>
<P>
 Granada Hills 3, El Camino Real 2 (3-2 penalty kicks) -- Darleen Valdivia 
scored twice in the second half to put the Highlanders (10-3-1) back in the 
match, then goaltender Danett Epstein stopped three of five penalty kicks in 
her first-ever shootout to propel Granada Hills to the semifinals. Epstein 
recorded six saves. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern Section (quarterfinals) 
</P>
<P>
 Buena 2, Mira Costa 1 -- Monica Almaraz scored the winning goal with 14 
minutes to play in a Division II match at Buena. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bulldogs (21-3-4) tied the score two minutes before halftime when Tammy 
Peck took a pass from Allyson Munday and put a shot past Mira Costa goalie 
Katie Eviston. Munday also assisted on Almaraz's goal. 
</P>
<P>
 La Serna 3, Hart 0 -- Lori Harris, Colby Morgan and Kim Keeney scored in the 
Division III match. 
</P>
<P>
 La Reina 2, Marlborough 0 -- Michelle Nuesca scored both second-half goals in 
the Division IV match at La Reina (22-2), giving her 86 for her career and 
breaking the school record of 84 set last season by Jaimie Armstrong. 
</P>
<P>
 Peninsula 1, Royal 0 -- The Highlanders (14-5-4) were shut out in a Division I 
match at Peninsula. 
</P>
