<TEXT>
<P>
 Soccer  
</P>
<P>
 The season appeared over for the San Fernando High boys' soccer team when it 
lost to South Gate, 3-2, last Friday in the first round of the City Section 
playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 But after inquiries by Tiger officials, South Gate was discovered to have used 
an ineligible player and had to forfeit its victory. 
