EAST VENTURA : MOORPARK; RUSTED PIPE BOMB FOUND NEXT TO HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County sheriff's deputies are investigating a pipe bomb found next to 
a Moorpark home that they believe was knocked off the roof while the house was 
being fumigated. 
</P>
<P>
 The device was found about 5 p.m. Wednesday between a house and detached 
garage in the 4200 block of Hitch Boulevard in Moorpark.It was retrieved by a 
member of the county bomb squad and disposed of at Camarillo Airport. 
</P>
<P>
 Detective Joe Braga said it appeared that the bomb fizzled out after someone 
lit the fuse months ago, although it was still capable of exploding. 
</P>
<P>
 Because of the rust on the pipe, Braga said he believed that the device sat on 
the roof for several months before it was knocked off by a tent placed atop the 
house for fumigation. Investigators have no suspects and no motive. JULIE 
FIELDS 
