<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; ADMINISTRATORS AT SCHOOLS ARE HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Administrators in the Ventura Unified School District have won awards in five 
out of 16 categories in an annual contest by the Assn. of California School 
Administrators' Region 13, which encompasses Ventura, Santa Barbara and San 
Luis Obispo counties. 
</P>
<P>
 Administrators who belong to the association give awards annually to peers who 
are considered to be the best in their jobs as principals or assistant 
principals or in other non-teaching positions. 
</P>
<P>
 This year, six winners were from Ventura County and five of the six were from 
the Ventura district. 
</P>
<P>
 Nancy Bradford, principal of Saticoy School, was named best elementary school 
principal in the region. Ventura High School Assistant Principal Helena 
Torrez-Reaves won the award for top assistant principal. Director of 
Certificated Personnel Jerry Dannenberg was honored as top personnel 
administrator. 
</P>
<P>
 Director of Administrative Services Arlene Miro won in the category for best 
central office administrator. And Valli Davis, who serves as secretary to Supt. 
Joseph Spirito, was honored as the best non-teaching employee who deals with 
confidential information. 
</P>
<P>
 The other regional winner in Ventura County was Gary Mortimer, a non-teaching 
employee in the Rio School District, Ventura school officials said. MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
