<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; SEBREROS HELPS FULLERTON EDGE CERRITOS IN NINTH 
INNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jimmy Sebreros' sacrifice fly in the ninth inning gave Fullerton a 6-5 victory 
over Cerritos in a nonconference baseball game Thursday at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton had scored two runs in the eighth inning to tie the score, 
5-5.Fullerton's Steve Escobar started the ninth-inning rally with a one-out 
single. Royce Valent singled and Wade Farley reached on an error to load the 
bases, bringing Sebreros to the plate. 
</P>
<P>
 Sebreros had three hits, including a triple, scored two runs, and drove in 
three more for Fullerton (6-5-1). Cerritos is 8-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonconference games: 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 6, Palomar 4 -- Kirk Irvine pitched eight innings to gain his 
second victory and host Rancho Santiago (11-2) won its eighth consecutive game. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach 8, Orange Coast 4 -- Richard Ernst had two doubles, scored a run 
and drove in another for host Orange Coast (3-5). OCC's Chris Yakura had three 
hits, including an RBI double. 
</P>
<P>
 Hancock 9, Golden West 8 (11 innings) -- Chad Myers had an RBI double in the 
11th for visiting Hancock (6-3). Rich Hughes had two hits and four RBIs for 
Golden West (6-5). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 4, Cerritos 3 -- Annie Presutti and April Crosby had two-run 
doubles for host OCC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
