BOYS' TENNIS / 1994 PREVIEW; SIX TEAMS TO WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dana Hills 
</P>
<P>
 Coach: John Stephens (sixth year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993: 14-8, 7-3 in the South Coast League; lost to University in the second 
round of Division I playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: David Bailey, Jr., could play No. 2 or 3 singles or No. 1 
doubles; Mike Baxi, Jr., could play singles or No. 1 or No. 2 doubles; Carlos 
Betancourt, Jr., will play No. 2 or No. 3 doubles; Hanley Ernst, Jr., 
ineligible last year, will play doubles this year; Erik Lundblad, Jr., should 
play No. 1 or No. 2 singles; Justin Rimel, Jr., will play doubles; Christian 
Spaulding, Sr., will play singles or No. 1 or No. 2 doubles. 
</P>
<P>
