could battle Lundblad for No. 1 singles spot. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: Stephens' lineup is fairly uncertain heading into the season. But the 
upside is that his team is blessed with plenty of talent. Stephens is 
especially excited about Fallon. "He's coming in with the most talent as a 
freshman that I've had in a number of years," Stephens said. It shouldn't take 
Stephens long to find out about his team. University, Corona del Mar, Newport 
Harbor, Woodbridge and Punahou (top-ranked Hawaiian team) are on the nonleague 
schedule. 
