<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATIONAL VIDEO RENTALS ; 'SEATTLE' A VALENTINE'S DAY DELIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Valentine's Day weekend rental run on "Sleepless in Seattle" finally 
boosted it into the top spot, toppling "The Firm," which slipped to No. 4. Of 
all the Top 10 rentals, "Sleepless" is the only one with strong romantic 
appeal, so it naturally benefited most from the holiday.It's also the kind of 
movie that does strong repeat business. "In the Line of Fire," the suspense 
thriller with Clint Eastwood, is next in line for the top spot. John 
Malkovich's supporting actor Oscar nomination is bound to elevate the movie's 
already-high rental appeal. "Kalifornia," a low-budget movie with Brad Pitt and 
Juliette Lewis, continues to do surprising business. Though racking up a small 
box-office gross, it inched up two more notches to No. 14, doing nearly as well 
as the expensive, heavily hyped "Coneheads," which has stalled at No. 11. 
Robert Townsend's "The Meteor Man," about a ghetto super-hero, isn't off to a 
blazing start, debuting at No. 31.  
</P>
<P>
 * Will all the promotion for Kim Basinger's new movie, "The Getaway," spill 
over and motivate renters to give this one a try? Movie-goers certainly never 
bothered with "The Real McCoy"--a true box-office dud with a $6.3-million 
gross. It's off to a modest rental-market start, at No. 21. 03,27,06,08 Rank 
Weeks Last on the Week Chart 1."Sleepless in Seattle" 2 9 2."Last Action Hero" 
5 3 3."Hard Target" 4 3 4."The Firm" 1 8 5."Dave" 3 8 6."In the Line of Fire" 
... 1 7."Rookie of the Year" 10 3 8."Rising Sun" 6 11 9."True Romance" 7 6 
10."Robin Hood: Men in Tights" 8 5 * "The Real McCoy" ... 1 Source: Billboard 
Publications Inc. DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
