</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 15-year-old boy was shot in the back Thursday at a high school campus in 
Whittier, the apparent victim of a gang attack, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting happened shortly after 4 p.m. when a group of youths in a car 
drove up to the victim as he stood on a playing field at Frontier High School, 
Whittier Police Lt. Dave Carlisle said . 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that one of the youths shouted gang names at the victim 
before shooting him with a .380-caliber handgun. The group fled in the car, 
which was found abandoned about an hour later in the 13500 block of Virginia 
Avenue just outside the city limits, Carlisle said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested the owner of the vehicle in connection with the shooting. 
Arturo Jimenez, 18, of Whittier was booked on suspicion of assault with a 
deadly weapon. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim was taken by helicopter to Martin Luther King Jr. Medical Center. 
No details of his condition were immediately available, a nursing supervisor 
said. 
</P>
