<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAM NOTES; RAMS MOVE TRAINING CAMP TO UC IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rams will move their training camp from Cal State Fullerton to UC Irvine 
this summer, according to university and team officials. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Novak, general counsel for the Rams, said Thursday that an agreement has 
been reached with UCI, and a contract is expected to be signed within a week or 
so. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams trained at Fullerton throughout the 1980s, but when construction of 
Fullerton's Titan Sports Complex began in the fall of 1990, the team moved its 
camp, which runs from mid-July to mid-August, to Irvine for 1991 and '92. The 
Rams returned to Fullerton last summer but were not happy with all of their 
accommodations. 
</P>
<P>
 "The facility at Fullerton is fine, but the whole arrangement at the 
University Village dorms was not a positive," Novak said. 
</P>
<P>
 Novak and Ed Carroll, UCI's associate athletic director for financial affairs, 
declined to discuss financial terms of the deal, but it's expected to be a boon 
to Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 "There's the publicity value of having them here, but we rent facilities all 
the time to generate revenue," Carroll said. "They pay for facility use, 
housing, food service, parking . . . it's a good chunk of change." MIKE 
DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
</TEXT>
