<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE SIGNINGS; EX-COUGAR KOSTOFF SIGNS TO PLAY BASKETBALL AT SCC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Guard Chris Kostoff has signed to play basketball at Southern California 
College, the school said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Kostoff, a graduate of Capistrano Valley, played the 1992-93 season for Irvine 
Valley and finished 12th in the state in scoring with a 22.5-point average. 
While at Capistrano Valley, he was All-Southern Section in 1990. He has two 
years of eligibility remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Rueter, a pitcher at Brethren Christian, has signed a letter of 
intent to play softball with Grace College of Winona Lake, Ind., an NAIA 
school. 
</P>
<P>
 Rueter was 5-5 last year with a 1.30 earned-run average with 119 strikeouts in 
89 2/3 innings. 
</P>
