<P>
BODY OF GIRL, 14, STOLEN WITHIN HOURS OF BURIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Grave robbers broke into a concrete vault and dug up the body of a 14-year-old 
girl within hours of her burial, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sara Anne Shick died on Feb. 18 of complications from a muscle disease and was 
buried Tuesday. That night, someone broke into a shed at the cemetery and used 
tools to break the seal around a concrete vault containing her casket. The 
vault, casket and tools were left behind. 
</P>
<P>
 A friend of the family reported the grave robbery Wednesday. Investigators had 
no leads, a Bonneville County sheriff's deputy said. 
