THE TIMES MUSIC INDEX : STACKING UP SALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Total album and single sales of CDs and cassettes for the week ended Feb. 20, 
compared to week-ago and year-ago levels, in millions of units sold:  
</P>
<P>
 Latest week: Albums: 11.0 Singles: 1.9 
</P>
<P>
 Week-ago: Albums: 9.9 Singles: 1.7 
</P>
<P>
 Year-ago: Albums: 9.6 Singles: 1.8 Hits Magazine Tip of the Week 
</P>
<P>
 Forget the mud. The road to Woodstock's 25th anniversary concert is proving 
bumpy.Insiders say research favors "traditional" Woodstock era artists such as 
Crosby, Stills & Nash and the Grateful Dead. But there is also pressure to 
include contemporary bands. Chatter has the concert lasting two days and 
incorporating "classic" and contemporary acts. Offers in the $250,000 range are 
said to have gone out to several bands, including Guns N' Roses, Metallica, 
Nirvana and Soundgarden. Plans for a video, film and record deal have also 
complicated booking plans. 
</P>
