BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 BASF Cuts Emissions: BASF Corp. said that it has greatly reduced emissions of 
17 chemicals at its U.S. plants, including one in Anaheim. The giant 
Parsippany, N.J.-based chemical company cut emissions by 60% at seven plants 
around the nation as part of a project run by the federal Environmental 
Protection Agency. That exceeds the goal of the Industrial Toxics Project, 
better known as "33/50," which calls for a 50% reduction by 1995. 
</P>
