<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUANTUM ADOPTS ANTI-TAKEOVER 'POISON PILL' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quantum Health Resources Inc. said Thursday it had adopted a "poison pill" to 
avert hostile takeovers. 
</P>
<P>
 Shareholders will be issued a right to buy one-hundredth of a share of a new 
preferred stock for each share of common stock the shareholder owns at a price 
of $100. 
</P>
<P>
 The rights are exercisable if a hostile suitor announced a tender offer or 
acquires 15% or more of the common stock. 
</P>
<P>
 Quantum is a leading national provider of health care to people with chronic 
diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
